Installation for IntelliJ
-------------------------

Copy `KnewtonStyle.xml` to the `codestyles` directory in your
preferences home.

On OS X, likely locations are:

    ~/Library/Preferences/IntelliJIdea12/codestyles
    ~/Library/Preferences/IdeaIC12/codestyles

To use the KnewtonStyle, navigate to the IntelliJ settings dialog,
go to Code Style > Java > Scheme, and select "KnewtonStyle"

To reformat code before you commit, use ALT+CMD+L on OS X, or
create configure your own bindings under the "Reformat Code" KeyMap.

Additional Changes
------------------

In the preferences:

   File Templates > Includes tab

Then, remove all pre-specified content and Apply changes.
